Laird Investors Seek Higher Cooper Offer, Sunday Times Reports

-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 
2011-06-26T09:01:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-26/laird-investors-seek-higher-cooper-offer-sunday-times-reports.html
Laird Plc (LRD)  investors said a bid of
210 pence ($3.36) a share would enable  Cooper Industries Plc (CBE)  to
gain access to its books, the  Sunday Times reported , citing
unidentified shareholders.  An offer in the range of 220 pence to 240 pence may enable
Cooper to take control of Laird, the London-based newspaper
cited the shareholders as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Armstrong at   parmstrong10@bloomberg.net  